# Portfolio Redesign Complete

I have successfully implemented all the requested changes to your portfolio website. The site has been upgraded with a modern, dynamic, and premium aesthetic, alongside new functional sections.

> [!TIP]
> You can preview these changes by starting your local Live Server (usually on port `5500` via VS Code). 

## What Changed?

### 1. CSS Overhaul (The "Wow" Factor)
- **Typography & Colors**: Migrated to the `Inter` font for a cleaner, modern look, while retaining `Parisienne` for your logo. The color palette has been refined, and extensive CSS variables were implemented to support Dark Mode.
- **Glassmorphism**: Applied glassmorphism techniques (semi-transparent backgrounds, blur filters, and subtle borders) to your Navbar, Cards, and Modals, giving them a premium, floating appearance.
- **Animations**: Added a floating particle background animation to the hero section (using purely CSS for performance), and implemented smooth slide-up animations for the Modals.
- **Project Cards**: Upgraded the project cards to include a sleek hover effect that darkens the image and slides up a "View Details" overlay.

### 2. Structural Additions (HTML)
- **Hero Section**: Restored the "View Portfolio" and "Download Resume" buttons to ensure clear calls to action.
- **Experience Timeline**: Added a new section just before the footer displaying your academic and professional journey in a clean, vertical timeline format.
- **Contact Form**: Implemented a comprehensive "Get In Touch" section featuring your contact details, social links, and a functional-looking form structure.

### 3. Interactive Polish (JavaScript)
- **Typed Text Effect**: The hero tagline now dynamically types out your various roles ("GIS Specialist", "Geospatial Data Analyst", etc.) using a custom JavaScript function.
- **Dark Mode Toggle**: A moon/sun toggle icon was added to the navigation bar. Clicking this switches the site to a carefully curated Dark Theme, saving the preference in `localStorage` so it persists across reloads.
- **Form Submission Simulation**: Added a small script to the contact form that changes the button state to "Sending..." and then "Message Sent!" to provide immediate feedback to users.

## Next Steps
- **Start your Live Server**: Right-click `index.html` in VS Code and select "Open with Live Server" to view the changes.
- **Test Responsiveness**: Resize your browser window to ensure the new Timeline and Contact sections look good on mobile devices.
- **Resume Link**: Ensure you have a `resume.pdf` file in the root directory, as the new "Download Resume" button points to it.
